      "I’ve been thinking about those tiny moments we share with strangers. The ones that flash by, barely enough time to trade names, yet months later they hang around my head with surprising weight. I forget lectures the moment I leave them, forget entire yap sessions with my friends (sorry sergio!), but a brief smile from a passerby in a foreign city clings to my memory. Why do those scraps of time feel so charged? Maybe it is because everything about them is fragile. They live outside routine. They owe us no next chapter, which makes their single page glow a little brighter.",
